HEADWORD: loupe
<hw>loupe</hw> <pr>(l⟦oomac⟧p)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>Any of a variety
of small magnifying glasses, having a magnifying power from 2X to 20X,
commonly of 10X, which may be held in the hand, or in some cases held
within the eyesocket without the use of a hand. It is commonly used by
jewelers and watchmakers.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

